{"body": "@rafaelfranca Only if the code that stored it put a boolean in there. In the app where this was extracted from, we needed to store a handful of boolean flags for each user (notification preferences) which needed to be edited via checkboxes. This got messy, since the form params came back with '0' or '1', both of which were truthy. \n\nHandling that would have meant either munging all the params in the controller (ugh), overriding all the `store_accessor` generated writers, overriding the readers, or pushing the \"'0' is false\" knowledge everywhere else in the code. ", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/8282028", "created_at": "2012-09-04T22:57:44Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/7524#issuecomment-8282028", "updated_at": "2012-09-04T22:57:44Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 7524, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/al2o3cr/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/al2o3cr/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/al2o3cr/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/al2o3cr", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/al2o3cr/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/al2o3cr", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/al2o3cr/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://0.gravatar.com/avatar/6883e5ef03484d4fcef507d7b4f1d243?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2Fb20bb95ab626d93fd976af958fbc61ba.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/al2o3cr/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/al2o3cr/received_events", "gravatar_id": "6883e5ef03484d4fcef507d7b4f1d243", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/al2o3cr/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "al2o3cr", "type": "User", "id": 1191, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/al2o3cr/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "523de4cebd354364b900b183"}, "id": 8282028, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/7524"}
